<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Workshops de Observabilidade on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/</link><description>Recent content in Workshops de Observabilidade on Splunk Observability Cloud Workshops</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>pt-BR</language><atom:link href="https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>1. APM Service Map</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/1-apm-service-map/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/1-apm-service-map/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;O APM Service Map exibe as dependências e conexões entre seus serviços instrumentados e inferidos em APM. O mapa é gerado dinamicamente com base nas suas seleções de intervalo de tempo, ambiente, transação de negócio, serviço e filtros de tags.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Quando clicamos no link de APM no waterfall de RUM, filtros foram adicionados automaticamente à visualização do service map para mostrar os serviços envolvidos naquela &lt;strong&gt;Transaction&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;code&gt;frontend:/cart/checkout&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Você pode ver os serviços envolvidos no workflow no &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt;. No painel lateral, são exibidos gráficos para a transação selecionada. Quando você seleciona um serviço no &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt;, os gráficos no painel lateral são atualizados para mostrar métricas do serviço selecionado.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>1. Dashboard de Synthetics</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/1-synthetics-dashboard/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/1-synthetics-dashboard/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Encontrar uma execução com falha em Synthetics&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;No Splunk Observability Cloud, no menu principal, clique em &lt;strong&gt;Digital Experience → Synthetics tests&lt;/strong&gt;. Clique em &lt;strong&gt;All&lt;/strong&gt; ou &lt;strong&gt;Browser tests&lt;/strong&gt; para ver a lista de testes ativos.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Durante nossa investigação na seção de RUM, encontramos um problema com a Transaction &lt;strong&gt;Place Order&lt;/strong&gt;. Vamos ver se também conseguimos confirmar isso pelo teste de Synthetics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Na caixa &lt;strong&gt;Search&lt;/strong&gt;, digite &lt;strong&gt;[NAME OF WORKSHOP]&lt;/strong&gt; para filtrar os testes deste workshop.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>1. Introdução a Logs</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/1-introduction/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/1-introduction/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Agora você navegou diretamente de um trace de &lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt; para &lt;strong&gt;Logs&lt;/strong&gt; usando o link de &lt;strong&gt;Related Content&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;strong&gt;Logs&lt;/strong&gt; é a interface no-code do Splunk Observability Cloud para explorar e analisar dados de logs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A principal vantagem, assim como na integração entre &lt;strong&gt;RUM&lt;/strong&gt; e &lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt;, é que você está vendo seus logs no contexto das ações anteriores. Neste caso, esse contexto inclui o intervalo de tempo correspondente &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt; do trace e um filtro &lt;strong&gt;(2)&lt;/strong&gt; aplicado automaticamente ao &lt;code&gt;trace_id&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Visão geral do RUM</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/1-rum-overview/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/1-rum-overview/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Filtrar para sua loja&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No Splunk Observability Cloud, no menu principal, passe o mouse sobre &lt;strong&gt;Digital Experience&lt;/strong&gt; e clique em &lt;strong&gt;Overview&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt; na seção &lt;strong&gt;Real User Monitoring&lt;/strong&gt;, como mostrado abaixo.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/rum-de.png" alt="RUM" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isso abrirá o &lt;strong&gt;Application Summary Dashboard&lt;/strong&gt;. Esta seção mostra uma visão rápida de &lt;strong&gt;todas&lt;/strong&gt; as aplicações monitoradas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O dashboard Real User Monitoring (RUM) Overview no Splunk Observability Cloud oferece visibilidade sobre como usuários reais experimentam suas aplicações web. Ele captura métricas de desempenho do navegador, erros de JavaScript e falhas em requisições de rede conforme ocorrem em sessões reais de usuários. O dashboard destaca Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) para medir o desempenho de carregamento das páginas, exibe tendências de erro ao longo do tempo e mostra alertas recentes, dando às equipes de front-end os insights necessários para identificar e corrigir problemas que afetam a experiência do usuário final.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. APM Service View</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/2-apm-service-view/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/2-apm-service-view/</guid><description>&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Service View&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="callout__body"&gt;Como responsável por um serviço, você pode usar a service view no Splunk APM para obter uma visão completa da saúde do seu serviço em um único painel. A service view inclui um indicador em nível de serviço (SLI) para disponibilidade, dependências, métricas de request, error e duration (RED), métricas de runtime, métricas de infraestrutura, Tag Spotlight, endpoints e logs para um serviço selecionado. Você também pode navegar rapidamente para code profiling e memory profiling do seu serviço a partir da service view.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Ampliar o período para expor erros&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confira a caixa &lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;. Você pode ver que os dashboards mostram apenas dados relevantes ao tempo que o trace de APM selecionado anteriormente levou para concluir (observe que os gráficos são estáticos).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Na caixa &lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;, altere o período para &lt;strong&gt;-1h&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-service-dashboard.png" alt="Service Dashboard" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Detalhe do teste de Synthetics</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/2-synthetics-detail/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/2-synthetics-detail/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Inspecionar o playback do teste&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agora estamos olhando para o resultado de um único Synthetic Browser Test.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/synth-waterfall.png" alt="waterfall" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Por padrão, Splunk Synthetics fornece capturas de tela e gravação em vídeo do teste. Isso é útil para depurar problemas. Você pode ver, por exemplo, o carregamento lento de imagens grandes, a renderização lenta de uma página etc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use o mouse para rolar para a esquerda e para a direita pela filmstrip e ver como o site estava sendo renderizado durante a execução do teste.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Filtro de Logs</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/2-log-filtering/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/2-log-filtering/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Filtrar para logs de erro&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Precisamos focar apenas nas mensagens de Error nos logs:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no menu suspenso &lt;strong&gt;Group By&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt; e use o filtro para encontrar &lt;strong&gt;severity&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Depois de selecionar, clique no botão &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; (observe que a legenda do gráfico muda para mostrar debug, error e info).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/severity-logs.png" alt="legend" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Para selecionar apenas os logs de erro, clique na palavra error &lt;strong&gt;(2)&lt;/strong&gt; na legenda e selecione &lt;strong&gt;Add to filter&lt;/strong&gt;. Em seguida, clique em &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Run Search&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; no topo da página.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/log-observer-errors.png" alt="Error Logs" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>2. Visualização da aplicação</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/2-rum-app-view/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/2-rum-app-view/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Explorar o dashboard de RUM&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agora você verá uma visualização de dashboard que detalha as métricas por &lt;strong&gt;UX Metrics&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Front-end Health&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Back-end Health&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Custom Events&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Network Requests&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;Pages&lt;/strong&gt; e uma &lt;strong&gt;Map View&lt;/strong&gt;, comparando tudo com métricas históricas (1 hora por padrão).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/rum-metric-map-charts.png" alt="RUM Dashboard" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As abas disponíveis nesta página incluem:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UX Metrics&lt;/strong&gt; Métricas de Page Views, Page Load e Web Vitals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Front-end Health&lt;/strong&gt; Detalhamento de JavaScript Errors e duração/contagem de Long Tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Back-end Health&lt;/strong&gt; Network Errors, Requests e Time to First Byte&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Custom Events&lt;/strong&gt; Métricas RED (Rate, Error e Duration) para eventos customizados&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Network Requests&lt;/strong&gt; Agrupamento de URLs de rede e métricas principais&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pages&lt;/strong&gt; Agrupamento de URLs, métricas principais e Web Vitals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Map View&lt;/strong&gt; Requisições geográficas por localização&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clique em cada uma das abas e examine os dados.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. APM Tag Spotlight</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/3-apm-tag-spotlight/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/3-apm-tag-spotlight/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Encontrar a versão ruim no Tag Spotlight&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ao entrar em &lt;strong&gt;Tag Spotlight&lt;/strong&gt;, garanta que o toggle &lt;strong&gt;Show tags with no values&lt;/strong&gt; esteja desligado.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-tag-spotlight.png" alt="APM Tag Spotlight" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Esta visualização exibe uma série de cards, cada um representando uma tag indexada (como Endpoint, Environment, Version ou tags customizadas como tenant.level). Dentro de cada card, você vê a distribuição dos valores da tag junto com métricas principais, incluindo contagem de requisições, contagem de erros, erros de causa raiz e percentis de latência (P50, P90, P99).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;Pergunta&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;Resposta&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qual card expõe a tag que identifica qual é o problema?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-3-apm-tag-spotlight-md-1-1--0-tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;O card &lt;em&gt;version&lt;/em&gt;. O número de requisições contra &lt;code&gt;v350.10&lt;/code&gt; corresponde ao número de erros, ou seja, 100%.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Agora que identificamos a tag que indica o problema, vamos ver se conseguimos encontrar mais informações sobre o erro.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no link &lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt; acima de &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; no topo da página para voltar para o &lt;strong&gt;APM Overview&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Em &lt;strong&gt;APM Overview&lt;/strong&gt;, clique em &lt;strong&gt;Service Map&lt;/strong&gt; no painel à direita.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Synthetics para APM</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/3-synthetics-to-apm/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/3-synthetics-to-apm/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Ir de Synthetics para APM&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No waterfall, encontre uma entrada que começa com &lt;strong&gt;POST checkout&lt;/strong&gt;. Se você não vir essa entrada, volte e selecione outro resultado com falha na página &lt;strong&gt;Run results&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/run-results-place-order.png" alt="Place Order" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique em &lt;strong&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt; para abrir a seção de metadados. Observe os metadados coletados e repare no header &lt;strong&gt;server-timing&lt;/strong&gt; em &lt;strong&gt;Response Headers&lt;/strong&gt;. Esse header é o que nos permite correlacionar a execução do teste com um trace de back-end.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no link azul &lt;span class="inline-icon"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M10 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"/&gt;&lt;path d="M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(2)&lt;/strong&gt; na linha &lt;strong&gt;POST checkout&lt;/strong&gt; do waterfall.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-trace.png" alt="APM trace" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Tag Spotlight</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/3-tag-spotlight/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/3-tag-spotlight/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Filtrar para sessões PlaceOrder lentas&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Este dashboard exibe todas as tags associadas aos dados de RUM, pares chave-valor gerados automaticamente pela instrumentação de RUM. Tags são usadas para filtrar dados e criar gráficos e tabelas. A visualização Tag Spotlight permite aprofundar a análise em sessões individuais de usuários.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/rum-tag-spotlight.png" alt="RUM Tag Spotlight" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Altere o período para &lt;strong&gt;Last 1 hour&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;!--* Clique em **Add Filters**, selecione **OS Version**, clique em **!=**, selecione **Synthetics** e **RUM.LoadGen** e então clique no botão &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: #1d5d99"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply Filter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; **(2)**.--&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Encontre o gráfico &lt;strong&gt;Operation&lt;/strong&gt;, localize &lt;strong&gt;PlaceOrder&lt;/strong&gt; na lista, clique nele e selecione &lt;strong&gt;Add to filter&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(2)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>3. Visualizar entradas de log</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/3-log-entry/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/5-logs/3-log-entry/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Abrir um log de erro&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique em uma entrada de erro na tabela de logs (garanta que ela diga &lt;code&gt;hostname: &amp;quot;paymentservice-xxxx&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;, caso também apareça algum erro raro de outro serviço na lista).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;Pergunta&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;Resposta&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-tab-0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Com base na mensagem, o que você diria à equipe de desenvolvimento para fazer e resolver o problema?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-5-logs-3-log-entry-md-1-1--0-tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A equipe de desenvolvimento precisa reconstruir e implantar o container com um API Token válido ou fazer rollback para &lt;code&gt;v350.9&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/log-observer-log-message.png" alt="Log Message" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. APM Service Breakdown</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/4-apm-service-breakdown/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/4-apm-service-breakdown/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Detalhar o serviço por versão&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selecione o &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; no Service Map.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No painel à direita, clique em &lt;button class="btn-inline btn-inline--filled" type="button" style="--btn-color: var(--color-ink-muted)"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Breakdown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selecione &lt;code&gt;version&lt;/code&gt; na lista.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs" data-tabs&gt;
&lt;div class="tabs__list" role="tablist"&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-0" class="tabs__btn is-active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-0" tabindex="0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;Pergunta&lt;/button&gt;&lt;button id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-1" class="tabs__btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-1" tabindex="-1" data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;Resposta&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-0" class="tabs__panel is-active" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-0" data-tab-label="Pergunta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;O que você pode concluir a partir do que está vendo?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-panel-1" class="tabs__panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tabs---home-runner-work-observability-workshop-observability-workshop-content-pt-br-splunk4rookies-observability-cloud-short-4-apm-4-apm-service-breakdown-md-1-1--1-tab-1" hidden data-tab-label="Resposta"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Não há erros para &lt;code&gt;v350.9&lt;/code&gt;, mas &lt;code&gt;v350.10&lt;/code&gt; claramente tem um problema.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/apm-service-breakdown.png" alt="APM Service Breakdown" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--info"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12" y2="12"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12.01" y2="8"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Span Tags&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. Detector de Synthetics</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/4-synthetics-detector/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/4-synthetics-detector/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Como você pode executar esses testes 24/7, eles são uma ferramenta ideal para receber avisos cedo quando seus testes estão falhando ou começando a demorar mais do que o SLA combinado, em vez de descobrir por redes sociais ou sites de uptime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/social-media-post.png" alt="Social media" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
 
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Para evitar que isso aconteça, vamos detectar se nosso teste está levando mais de 50 segundos.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>4. User Sessions</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/4-user-sessions/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/4-user-sessions/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Uma &lt;strong&gt;User Session&lt;/strong&gt; no RUM representa a interação completa de um único usuário com sua aplicação web, desde o momento em que ele chega até sair ou ficar inativo. Cada sessão captura uma linha do tempo com todas as visualizações de página, interações do usuário (cliques, rolagens, envios de formulário), requisições de rede, erros e métricas de desempenho.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As sessões são identificadas por um Session ID único e incluem metadados como tipo de navegador, dispositivo, localização geográfica e tags customizadas. Isso permite reproduzir e analisar a experiência exata de um usuário específico, o que é muito valioso para troubleshooting, entendimento do comportamento do usuário e identificação de gargalos de desempenho.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. APM Trace Analyzer</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/5-apm-trace-analyzer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/5-apm-trace-analyzer/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Chegamos ao &lt;strong&gt;Trace Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O &lt;strong&gt;Trace Analyzer&lt;/strong&gt; é uma ferramenta poderosa do Splunk APM para explorar e analisar traces distribuídos em escala. Como o Splunk APM captura todos os traces com fidelidade completa (NoSample), você tem visibilidade total de todas as transações que passam pelos seus serviços.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;O Trace Analyzer permite:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pesquisar com tags de alta cardinalidade&lt;/strong&gt;: filtre traces usando qualquer span tag indexada, como IDs de cliente, IDs de pedido ou atributos customizados de negócio.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visualizar padrões de trace&lt;/strong&gt;: veja contagens de traces e erros ao longo do tempo para identificar tendências e anomalias.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analisar a distribuição de latência&lt;/strong&gt;: use a visualização de heatmap para entender padrões de duração dos traces e localizar outliers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Aprofundar em traces específicos&lt;/strong&gt;: encontre rapidamente o trace exato de que você precisa, seja para investigar uma reclamação de cliente ou depurar uma transação específica.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Isso torna o Trace Analyzer ideal para investigar problemas desconhecidos, pesquisar transações específicas e fazer análise de causa raiz quando você precisa encontrar uma agulha no palheiro.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. Criar Detector</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/5-create-detector/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/6-synthetics/5-create-detector/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Receber alertas&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Vá para &lt;strong&gt;Digital Experience → Synthetics tests&lt;/strong&gt; no menu principal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Selecione o teste do workshop &lt;strong&gt;[NAME OF WORKSHOP]&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no teste.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clique no botão &lt;button class="btn-inline" type="button"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create Detector&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/button&gt; no topo da página:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Altere os critérios de alerta para que a métrica seja &lt;strong&gt;Run Duration&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(1)&lt;/strong&gt; (em vez de Uptime) e a condição seja &lt;strong&gt;Static Threshold&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defina o &lt;strong&gt;Trigger threshold&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(2)&lt;/strong&gt; para algo em torno de &lt;code&gt;50000&lt;/code&gt; ms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defina &lt;strong&gt;Split by location&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(3)&lt;/strong&gt; como &lt;strong&gt;No&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observe que agora há uma linha de triângulos vermelhos e brancos aparecendo abaixo dos picos no gráfico.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Os triângulos vermelhos indicam que o detector encontrou seu teste acima do limite definido, e o triângulo branco indica que o resultado voltou para baixo do limite. Cada triângulo vermelho disparará um alerta.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class="callout callout--warning"&gt;&lt;span class="callout__icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;path d="M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"/&gt;&lt;line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p class="callout__title"&gt;Não adicionaremos um destinatário nem ativaremos o detector, pois não queremos inundar seu e-mail com alertas.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>5. RUM para APM</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/5-rum-to-apm/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/3-rum/5-rum-to-apm/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Localizar o serviço com falha&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;No &lt;strong&gt;APM Service Map&lt;/strong&gt;, você consegue ver claramente que há um problema com o &lt;code&gt;paymentservice&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;figure class="figure"&gt;
 &lt;div class="figure__inner"&gt;
 &lt;img src="../images/rum-to-apm.png" alt="RUM to APM" loading="lazy" decoding="async"&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agora navegamos com sucesso de &lt;strong&gt;RUM&lt;/strong&gt; para &lt;strong&gt;APM&lt;/strong&gt;, obtendo uma visão de ponta a ponta da experiência do usuário. Essa integração permite rastrear problemas de desempenho desde o front-end até os serviços de back-end, tornando o troubleshooting e a otimização mais eficazes.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>6. APM Waterfall</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/6-apm-waterfall/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/6-apm-waterfall/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;A visualização &lt;strong&gt;Trace Waterfall&lt;/strong&gt; mostra todos os spans de um trace como uma linha do tempo hierárquica. Cada span aparece como uma barra horizontal, em que o comprimento da barra representa sua duração e sua posição mostra quando ele ocorreu em relação aos outros spans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Um trace é uma coleção de spans que compartilham o mesmo trace ID, representando uma transação única processada pela sua aplicação e pelos serviços que a compõem.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>7. APM para Logs</title><link>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/7-apm-to-logs/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://splunk.github.io/observability-workshop/pt-br/splunk4rookies/observability-cloud-short/4-apm/7-apm-to-logs/</guid><description>&lt;section class="exercise"&gt;
&lt;header class="exercise__bar"&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-icon" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="6"/&gt;&lt;circle cx="12" cy="12" r="2"/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-label"&gt;Exercício&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-divider" aria-hidden="true"&gt;·&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="exercise__bar-title"&gt;Ir de APM para Related Logs&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/header&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__panel"&gt;
&lt;div class="exercise__body"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agora que identificamos a versão do &lt;strong&gt;paymentservice&lt;/strong&gt; que está causando o problema, vamos ver se conseguimos encontrar mais informações sobre o erro. É aqui que entram os &lt;strong&gt;Related Logs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Related Content depende de metadados específicos que permitem que APM, Infrastructure Monitoring e Log Observer passem filtros entre áreas do Observability Cloud. Para que logs relacionados funcionem, você precisa ter os seguintes metadados nos seus logs:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>